Ingredients
2 cups dried chickpeas
½ tsp baking soda
1 cup fresh parsley leaves
¾ cup fresh cilantro leaves
½ cup fresh dill
1 small onion
7-8 garlic cloves
Salt to taste
1 tbsp ground black pepper
1 tbsp ground cumin
1 tbsp ground coriander
1 tsp cayenne pepper
1 tsp baking powder
2 tbsp toasted sesame seeds
Oil for frying





Method
Soak chickpeas for 12-18 hours along with some baking soda

Mix chickpeas along with rest of the ingredients in a mixer

Remove into a bowl and refrigerate for 1-2 hours

Add baking powder and sesame seeds before frying






